    public class ItemInstance
extends DomainResource
    A physical, countable instance of an item, for example one box or one unit.

      • getCountElement

        public IntegerType getCountElement()
        Returns:
        count (The quantity or amount of instances. For example if several units are being counted for inventory, this quantity can be more than one, provided they are not unique. Seriallized items are considered unique and as such would have a quantity max 1. This element is required and its presence asserts that the reource refers to a physical item.). This is the underlying object with id, value and extensions. The accessor "getCount" gives direct access to the value

      • getCount

        public int getCount()
        Returns:

Seriallized items are considered unique and as such would have a quantity max 1. This element is required and its presence asserts that the reource refers to a physical item.
